<subSubSection id="02C66578FFE2FFA3FF3D9B0C6BF9757C" pageId="15" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFE2FFA3FF3D9B0C68987ADF" blockId="15.[151,756,1864,2077]" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFE2FFA3FF3D9B0C68057A01" bold="true" box="[151,264,1864,1888]" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">Remarks:</emphasis>
It is characterized by an elongate test having a pyramidal shape. The test is triserial and its chambers are numerous rather indistinct, not inflated and increasing slowly in size as added.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFE2FFA3FF3D9B826BF9757C" blockId="15.[151,756,1864,2077]" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFE2FFA3FF3D9B8268D87ABF" bold="true" box="[151,469,1990,2014]" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It is recorded in the Maastrichtian by SAID &amp; KENAWY (1953). In the study area, it is floody in the Maastrichtian zones
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
